---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead />
    <SEO
      title={title}
      description="Full-Stack Engineer with a strong focus on type-safety"
      openGraph={{
        basic: {
          type: 'website',
          title,
          url: 'https://ivanpartida.xyz',
          image: ogImage,
        },
        optional: {
          description,
        },
      }}
      twitter={{
        card: 'summary_large_image',
        site: '@DeadOce4n',
        title,
        description,
        image: ogImage,
        creator: '@DeadOce4n',
      }}
    />
  </head>
  <Layout>
    <section>
      <h1 class="not-prose mb-2">
        <span
          class="from-purple to-pink bg-gradient-to-r bg-clip-text text-transparent"
        >
          Hi, I'm Ivan Partida
        </span>
        <span class="animate-wiggle inline-block">ðŸ‘‹</span>
      </h1>
      <span class="text-white-dark mb-4 inline-block text-sm font-bold italic">
        Full-Stack Engineer with a focus on <span
          class="decoration-red whitespace-nowrap underline decoration-wavy"
          >type-safety</span
        > and tooling
      </span>
      <p>
        I love all things web-dev related: frontend development with <InlineWithIcon
          icon={React}
          text="React"
          color="blue"
        />
         and <InlineWithIcon text="Svelte" icon={Svelte} color="orange" />,
        backend development with <InlineWithIcon
          text="Node.js"
          icon={NodeJs}
          color="green"
        /> and <InlineWithIcon text="Python" icon={Python} color="yellow" />,
        and I can work comfortably in (almost) any part of the stack.
      </p>
      <p>
        My favorite programming language is <InlineWithIcon
          text="TypeScript"
          icon={TypeScript}
          color="blue"
        />, so much that I even use it for DevOps (which I am in love with but
        have barely scratched the surface)! Given the complexity of modern web
        apps, I think full-stack type-safety is a must.
      </p>
      <p>
        I also love the terminal, so I use a lot of CLI and TUI tools on a daily
        basis. <InlineWithIcon text="Neovim" icon={NeoVim} color="green" />
         is my favorite text editor because it allows me to code
        <em>blazingly fast</em>.
      </p>
    </section>
    <CurrentlyEditing client:load />
    <section>
      <h2>Work experience</h2>
      <div class="mb-8 px-4 pt-4">
        <WorkExpEntry
          employer="G-Global"
          jobTitle="Full-Stack Developer - DevOps Engineer"
          period="May 2022 - Present"
        >
          <ul class="ml-4">
            <li>
              Contributed to the development and maintenance of the company's
              internal software products.
            </li>
            <li>
              Improved the team's overall development experience by
              standardizing the development toolchain and mentoring other team
              members about its correct usage.
            </li>
            <li>
              Shortened the time to production for all of the company's products
              significantly by developing a tool for massively deploying and
              managing microservices through the <InlineWithIcon
                text="GitLab"
                icon={GitLab}
                color="orange"
              />
